Back in 2003, 2 years before So You Think You Can Dance first aired, many years before social media existed, hell…even 4 years before the 1st iPhone came out…there was a TV show featuring a stand-out character that changed my life forever. 

The Wade Robson Project on MTV was the 1st of it’s kind for kids like me. A dance show based on freestyle & commercial choreography featuring the best in the industry. I’d find myself racing home after school (at Woburn High) to catch it before going to a full day of dance training to then later watch the rerun episode at 11:30pm that same night every single time it was on. The big draw of the show was this one guy that absolutely blew my mind unlike anything I’d ever seen before. His name was Stephen “Twitch” Boss.

An explosive, freak-of-nature kind of talent with a very unique style. Twitch was incredibly cool, edgy, and had a charisma that beamed through the screen into everyone’s living rooms. He could do hip hop, had technique, and performed with a command that was undeniably captivating. I was instantly inspired. 

Point Blank: Seeing @sir_twitch_alot made me want to pursue dance professionally. 

Although we were more of acquaintances, when we’d see each-other around, you were always welcoming, kind, and present in conversation. I’ll never forget the season we worked together when I was assisting Luther Brown on a particular episode of SYTCD and you were a returning all-star on the show. Being in the studio and on set with you that week was one of the highlights in my dance career that my high school-self was literally to the moon over! Getting to work with one of the main guys that inspired it all..c’mon! I’ll never forget the personable demeanor, professionalism, and incredible energy you exuded throughout that experience. 

My story is just one of so many between all of the people whom you’ve had such a positive influence on over the years. That is a true testament to who Twitch was. Thank you for being the inspiration, light, and role model you were to me as well the entire world. 

Rest in Power @sir_twitch_alot 
Sending so much love and condolences to Allison, their children, and the entire Boss family. 🕊️♥️🙏

Everything about this experience was full circle!🍿 🎞️ ⭐️ #IWDWS #whitneyhouston 

Shooting this iconic movie in Boston is goal I’ve always wanted to check off the list, but getting to watch it here made it that much better! A couple months ago, I was able to go to the same movie theater I used to go to in my adolescent years to watch a feature film that I’m in with people I love the most. 

I’ve hung out at Woburn Showcase Cinemas as far back as I can remember. The wholesome elementary school years to the badass middle school ones to the even more meddling high school days. If you’re from Woburn, ykyk.

I got to work with my best friend for so many years (from the same damn area), @ianj_mckenzie. I was hired by long time friend @jamesals0p that killed this project (as she always does with everything she touches!). Thank you, James! I got to work alongside legends like @ebonywilliamsworld, inspirations like @oliviacipolla, and danced with the new upcoming generation. The whole experience was smooth and beyond inspirational. I also have to add ##naomiackie was a complete ray of sunshine and lit up the entire room all throughout the process! 

At this point in my career, there’s always the constant waves of the highs and lows that come with being in this industry, but I’ve always believed in the fact that I’m an artist placed right in the exact place the universe wants me to be in at that very time along my journey in life. Every component of this project highlighted that:

Home. Family. Career. Friends. Love. 🫶

Freestyle 🎥’d by @missandyej 

I definitely consider myself an “unorthodox kind-of mover”. 

I have the type of style that either you really like it or you really don’t lol, and I’m okay with that. ✌️ 

Over time I can be honest and say there’s been moments where I don’t know particularly where I fit in the dance world. I’m not saying this in a negative way. It’s just between the commercial kids, freestylers, and any hybrid in between I have always felt like an outsider. On the flip-side of that, I’ve always embraced the outsider role and in return it has allowed me to have the creative freedom to work with any and everybody I come across with no restrictions! 

The main thing I’m trying to say out of all of this is I do this for a purest of loves of the art form and connecting around the world with people that care about it as much as I do, and nothing will stop that. Stay true to who you are no matter what!!! 

A million thank you’s to my @monstersdance family and everyone else for the genuine support over all these years! 

Best, 
- AF 👽

Last week, I tapped into the deepest part of my consciousness more than I ever have before. 🧊🧘‍♂️🏔️ 

I have been practicing the #wimhofmethod consistently for 3 straight years now (1st started playing around with it sporadically in 2018). The #wimhofwinterexpedition in the frigid mountains of Poland is something I’ve been dreaming of doing for quite some time. I can finally say I completed this goal. 

This was by far the most incredible, yet mental, physical, and (uplifting) spiritual experience I’ve ever taken part of. 

Thank you @iceman_hof for the inspiration that you are and providing this experience, to my group instructors @openmind_inc @gittelindgaard, and my group, the Purple Team (Weirdos United), we will have this forever! 

I’m beyond grateful for this method as it’s changed my life. Thankful for this journey as it seemed outside of my wildest dreams. So Appreciative of the blessing and privilege it was to be here in flow for 5 days. Still doesn’t feel real! 

Slide 1: Super Mario jump after 3 hour hike (1 way up) in 35 degree F rain - Finished in 15 degree (negative wind chill) F in snow covered mountains 🏔️ 

Slide 2: 7 meter (20 ft) cliff jump into ice cold water - waited about 45 min-1 hour (in bathing suit) before jumping ☃️

Slide 3: Weirdos United (purple team) group photo at the end of 3 hour hike in Polish snow covered mountains (in shorts & boots). Love these guys!!! 💜

Slide 4: Last group session at Wim’s house led by Gitte & Yury 📓

Slide 5: Loading in for the first 5 minute ice plunge (of the trip) in snowing conditions. Water temp around 34 degrees F in rushing river 🧊 

Slide 6: Bonus 3-5 minute night ice plunge for @marecko bday! Water temp: colder than anything you can imagine lol 🌙 🧊 

Slide 7: Sun Salutations morning yoga w/ Yury 🧘‍♂️ 

Slide 8: getting ready for seminar/breathing-excercises with Wim (couldn’t believe I was actually getting to do this) 🤯

Slide 9: Outdoor breath-work session - (brown-fat activation) in just shorts & boots. Outside temp: 34 degrees F 🌲

#alexfetbrothchoreography 

I had the honor of teaching the advanced room audition this weekend. For anyone who knows about the #monstershow rehearsal(s) experience, the biggest challenge is having to learn an insane amount of material in a condensed amount of time (multiple times of the day) with many different all-star professional choreographers over a span of 2 weeks cultivating to performing a full weekend show for the masses. It’s essentially a dancer’s hardest marathon mentally, physically, and spiritually. 

Considering I had the advanced room, I didn’t want to do just 6-8 eight’s (as a standard audition may call for), but really give a simulation of what it can feel like if you get into Monsters Show rehearsals. The dancers learned 1:20 of choreography as we dove deep into our will and made it to the other side elevated! Really proud of you all. 🙌

Sending a huge THANK YOU to #monstersalumni @__.nmakinghistory for assisting me throughout this whole process and being such a pro’s pro! 🙏

This past weekend I had the honor of teaching the XX industry class at @monstersdance #newbrunswick.

My premise for this class was for the students to perform in a in visually immersive piece like something you might see at at an art exhibition at a museum or show ar a theater. I called it “visual playground” where the dancers would react (through their performance) simultaneously to the screen (to the left of the stage) whether it be movement, acting, staging, prop work, and audience interaction. They did everything from throwing bodies around to sound cues (with no counts), working with flashlights, getting in the audience’s face to standing in front of an industrial fan (you can see the wind blowing if you very closely at their shirts lol). 

The theme was simple: People were going to be battling a giant floating head (weird, yes). The “giant floating head” symbolizes our own minds and the thoughts/power it can have over us (positive and negative) while also recognizing WE have that same power to conquer own minds. The piece is a metaphor of that journey. 

We had to accomplish this experiment all within a 2 hour session including 29 people and I couldn’t have been any happier with how it turned out! Proud of each and every single dancer in here for being open, stepping outside of their comfort zone, and delivering a great ending piece of art! 

Thank you to @_regendary for filming/editing this, to @piinklemonade_ for being the force that you are, @marcobeheluli for editing the music, @lilmack_5678 for the assist, the best confidant anyone could ask for @missandyej, and of course my #monsters fam for allowing me the creative space and freedom to do this! 

Love.
Light.
Power. 
-AF

This year was one, if not the most special Monsters experiences I’ve ever gotten to be a part of. The powerful energy that came along with the landmark that is the 20th anniversary of the company coinciding with the hip hop’s 50th anniversary showed out in full force for this year’s show!

2023 CAST: I’ll never forget this experience that we had together. The centered focus around this show taking place in the Baltimore rehearsals to the fresh new energy that New York demanded was a journey I am beyond honored to have been by your side. WELCOME TO THE FAMILY!

Andy & Becky Funk: It all starts with you. THANK YOU for providing 20 years of excellence and genuine loving care for your people. You truly are top-notch human-beings that have opened so many doors for so many artists like myself!

Demoura: NO-ONE could have put on this show the way you did man! You are a TRUE director, leader, and creative. Your work-ethic/drive is admirable and I haven’t been this inspired coming off a project in a long time. It was an honor working alongside you bro. 

Andye J: YOU are the 1, 2, and the 3! I can’t believe how many hats you wore throughout this process and were still unbelievably attentive, organized, and exceptional in all of your duties. Your attention to detail is unmatched and your care for everyone that walks through the MOHH door says so much about your character. I’ll always cherish these days working together. 

Nikki: Working with you was one of the most fun, productive, and rewarding experiences ever! You truly are phenomenal and add so much value to any setting! This is literally my favorite piece to date and it would have never been what it is without you. THANK YOU! 

Riye & Kerrie: Riye, thank you so much for your help in rehearsals between demonstrating and cleaning. Kerrie, I’m so glad we got to reconnect in the way we did my friend! Thank you for being a support in tech’s in NY. 

Gene, Sierra, Nate, Jake, LT, Marco, Kenny, Bean: Monsters would never be what it is without all of you. You’re all consummate professionals and this ship only runs the way it does because of your different expertises combined. You are the glue to this thing!

Nothing inspires me more than being in a room with highly skilled individuals that passionately care about their craft! 

For the past 3 weeks, my experience has been exactly that.  I worked with the best of the best from rehearsals in LA all the way to production rehearsals and the big showtime in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. @nickdemoura the standards you set are next level. 

The #battleofthebaddest opening ceremony for the Francis Ngannou-Tyson Fury boxing match was one for the books. On top of being at this historic event across the world, I reunited in a performance with @iambeckyg and got down with @lilbaby & @big_flowdan on some fire pieces. Big shoutouts to Nicky D @mightymykell @tuckerbarkley @jblazeofficial on the crazy choreography created on this job!!! To my castmates, y’all are incredible and elevated me in every way possible! 

Show up as your best. Do your best. Become your best.
